Context: George Brown College offers university level (U-Level) courses for math, English, biology, and general science at a self-paced cost of $723.60 through their ACE Distance partners. The college has adult day and night schools available throughout the city offering full time and part time options with intakes available throughout the year. One-on-one sessions with advisors are available online, in-person, by phone, or by email, as well as workshops and information sessions to help navigate educational programs and pathways. The contact information for the college is 416-415-2000 (TTY: 1-877-515-5559) and ask.george@georgebrown.ca, with a social media hub also available. It's important to note that some programs may have admission requirements and competition. The information on the website is subject to change without notice.
